content: Hi <@1273823886433194008>, you should have a DM from Roberta. But you also have a confusing situation with two Discord accounts - so the DM is probably at the other account.
What do I do about the two accounts?
Good question, do you want both? Which one do you want to use?
I would prefer to only have one account.

Your other account is already onboarded, so I suggest switching to that, if you can and remember how to log into it. If you are on a computer, you may be able to switch by clicking on your profile icon in the lower left corner of the app window, then going to Switch Accounts. You can leave the server with this one.
What do I do with the switch accounts window?
When I go to switch accounts, I see both of my accounts listed and can click on the one that I want active. Do you see more than one account?
Do you remember how to log in to the other account?
Should I log out of it?  I think I can log into the other account.

If you think you can log into the other account, then I think you can just log into it in a browser window, rather than the app. If I remember correctly, when I did that I had, at some point, the option to open that account in the app.
Is there any way for you to delete one of them?

I can't delete one of them for you. You *can* leave the server with one of them. If you'd rather use this account, since it is logged in, then I can straighten things out on our end, I think, other than having you leave the server.
That would be great.  Sorry, but this is very confusing for me.
OK, I'll see what I can do.
OK, I have added you, removed the other account from the text team, and sent you a DM with some info.
I'm not sure what we'll do about the other account, it may just sit around.
